  <h2 id="opportunity-attributes-1" class="govuk-heading-m app-summary-list-heading">Overview</h2>
  
  

  

  

  

  

  

  

  
<dl class="govuk-summary-list app-govuk-summary-list app-govuk-summary-list--top-border govuk-!-margin-bottom-8">
  
    
      <div class="govuk-summary-list__row">
        <dt class="govuk-summary-list__key">
          Off-payroll (IR35) determination
        </dt>
        <dd class="govuk-summary-list__value">
          Contracted out service: the off-payroll rules do not apply
        </dd>
        
      </div>
    
  
    
      <div class="govuk-summary-list__row">
        <dt class="govuk-summary-list__key">
          Summary of the work
        </dt>
        <dd class="govuk-summary-list__value">
          Transformation through appropriate, strategic digitisation in order that women, children and families are enabled and empowered to take the lead in their pregnancy or health journey. Primarily through the creation of Digital Personal Health Records in which women, children and their families can interact with information and potentially service providers.
        </dd>
        
      </div>
    
  
    
      <div class="govuk-summary-list__row">
        <dt class="govuk-summary-list__key">
          Latest start date
        </dt>
        <dd class="govuk-summary-list__value">
          Monday 15 November 2021
        </dd>
        
      </div>
    
  
    
      <div class="govuk-summary-list__row">
        <dt class="govuk-summary-list__key">
          Expected contract length
        </dt>
        <dd class="govuk-summary-list__value">
          18 months
        </dd>
        
      </div>
    
  
    
      <div class="govuk-summary-list__row">
        <dt class="govuk-summary-list__key">
          Location
        </dt>
        <dd class="govuk-summary-list__value">
          No specific location, for example they can work remotely
        </dd>
        
      </div>
    
  
    
      <div class="govuk-summary-list__row">
        <dt class="govuk-summary-list__key">
          Organisation the work is for
        </dt>
        <dd class="govuk-summary-list__value">
          NHSX (Contracting Authority will be NHS England on behalf of NHSX)
        </dd>
        
      </div>
    
  
    
      <div class="govuk-summary-list__row">
        <dt class="govuk-summary-list__key">
          Budget range
        </dt>
        <dd class="govuk-summary-list__value">
          Maximum budget for discovery and alpha is £4,500,000.00
        </dd>
        
      </div>
    
  
</dl>

  <h2 id="opportunity-attributes-2" class="govuk-heading-m app-summary-list-heading">About the work</h2>
  
  

  

  

  

  

  

  

  
<dl class="govuk-summary-list app-govuk-summary-list app-govuk-summary-list--top-border govuk-!-margin-bottom-8">
  
    
      <div class="govuk-summary-list__row">
        <dt class="govuk-summary-list__key">
          Why the work is being done
        </dt>
        <dd class="govuk-summary-list__value">
          The NHSX Digital Transformation team supports the health and care system to realise the benefits of digital, data and technology to deliver better end to end services for their users and the professionals who deliver them. We support and enable teams across health and care with the design and delivery of simpler, faster and better end to end services. <br>We also build capability to help all relevant teams and organisations to understand why and how to deliver user centred digital and technology enabled services.
        </dd>
        
      </div>
    
  
    
      <div class="govuk-summary-list__row">
        <dt class="govuk-summary-list__key">
          Problem to be solved
        </dt>
        <dd class="govuk-summary-list__value">
          Delivery of Digital Child Health solutions to ensure that information relating to the digital child health pathway is captured electronically and shared with those who have an active interest in the data. Delivery of the Digital Maternity solutions to ensure that information relating to the maternity pathway is captured electronically, shared with those who have an active interest in the data and put in the hands of the mother.
        </dd>
        
      </div>
    
  
    
      <div class="govuk-summary-list__row">
        <dt class="govuk-summary-list__key">
          Who the users are and what they need to do
        </dt>
        <dd class="govuk-summary-list__value">
          As an expectant mother, then mother (or other family member) I need to track the progress of my pregnancy then my child’s development, so that I have a digital record of all relevant health information including: appointments, key dates and milestones.
        </dd>
        
      </div>
    
  
    
      <div class="govuk-summary-list__row">
        <dt class="govuk-summary-list__key">
          Early market engagement
        </dt>
        <dd class="govuk-summary-list__value">
          
        </dd>
        
      </div>
    
  
    
      <div class="govuk-summary-list__row">
        <dt class="govuk-summary-list__key">
          Any work that’s already been done
        </dt>
        <dd class="govuk-summary-list__value">
          A phase of work for the Digital Child Health programme took place during 2019/20 and partially into 2020/21.  This work did not deliver the required outcomes and was subsequently closed before the current  programme was opened. There is collateral in existence for the programme including user stories, national systems and system supplier engagement. For Digital Maternity, a programme of work was planned which produced a specification for a maternity services data set for secondary uses.  A wider programme was envisaged but was never initiated.
        </dd>
        
      </div>
    
  
    
      <div class="govuk-summary-list__row">
        <dt class="govuk-summary-list__key">
          Existing team
        </dt>
        <dd class="govuk-summary-list__value">
          An NHSX led, mixed team. Including representation from: NHS Digital, contractors, agencies and other stakeholders.
        </dd>
        
      </div>
    
  
    
      <div class="govuk-summary-list__row">
        <dt class="govuk-summary-list__key">
          Current phase
        </dt>
        <dd class="govuk-summary-list__value">
          Discovery
        </dd>
        
      </div>
    
  
</dl>

  <h2 id="opportunity-attributes-3" class="govuk-heading-m app-summary-list-heading">Work setup</h2>
  
  

  

  

  
<dl class="govuk-summary-list app-govuk-summary-list app-govuk-summary-list--top-border govuk-!-margin-bottom-8">
  
    
      <div class="govuk-summary-list__row">
        <dt class="govuk-summary-list__key">
          Address where the work will take place
        </dt>
        <dd class="govuk-summary-list__value">
          Remote working with potential meetings in Skipton House, London or Quarry House, Leeds.
        </dd>
        
      </div>
    
  
    
      <div class="govuk-summary-list__row">
        <dt class="govuk-summary-list__key">
          Working arrangements
        </dt>
        <dd class="govuk-summary-list__value">
          A flexible approach is required to meet the needs of each individual project and programme on a SoR (Statement of Requirements) basis. <br>Work may be carried out from multiple locations including the Supplier’s offices. Attendance at NHSX offices in London and in other locations around England may be required for meetings. <br>Given the potential impact on local services over the next few months, user research and design activities might need to be carried out remotely.
        </dd>
        
      </div>
    
  
    
      <div class="govuk-summary-list__row">
        <dt class="govuk-summary-list__key">
          Security clearance
        </dt>
        <dd class="govuk-summary-list__value">
          
        </dd>
        
      </div>
    
  
</dl>

