  <h2 id="opportunity-attributes-5" class="govuk-heading-m app-summary-list-heading">Skills and experience</h2>
  
  <p class="govuk-body govuk-!-margin-top-3">Buyers will use the essential and nice-to-have skills and experience to help them evaluate suppliers’ technical competence.</p>
  
  

  

  
<dl class="govuk-summary-list app-govuk-summary-list app-govuk-summary-list--top-border govuk-!-margin-bottom-8">
  
    
      <div class="govuk-summary-list__row">
        <dt class="govuk-summary-list__key">
          Essential skills and experience
        </dt>
        <dd class="govuk-summary-list__value">
          <ul class="govuk-list govuk-list--bullet">
          <li>Demonstrate successfully leading strategic, user-centred design work to understand the end-to-end lived experience of users and the professionals who deliver services.</li>
          <li>Demonstrate experience of using service design or user research insights to influence long-term organisation strategy or the approach of senior/board level decision makers.</li>
          <li>Demonstrate a full understanding and demonstrable experience of a wide range of research and design methodologies for designing high-volume digital services which have a diverse mix of users.</li>
          <li>Demonstrate an ability to scale the team to lead on further discoveries or alphas alongside existing discovery and alpha projects (with appropriate notice/agreement of work packages).</li>
          <li>Demonstrate recent experience (within the last 2 years) of designing and prototyping digital services that meet NHS and/or government service standards.</li>
          <li>Demonstrate recent (within the last 2 years) experience of recruiting a diverse workforce and promoting a supportive and inclusive culture.</li>
        </ul>
        </dd>
        
      </div>
    
  
    
      <div class="govuk-summary-list__row">
        <dt class="govuk-summary-list__key">
          Nice-to-have skills and experience
        </dt>
        <dd class="govuk-summary-list__value">
          <ul class="govuk-list govuk-list--bullet">
          <li>Demonstrate understanding and previous experience working with health, social care or local government services.</li>
          <li>Demonstrate understanding of when and how to use different types of and fidelity of artefacts and prototypes to validate concepts and communicate and get buy-in from a range of stakeholders.</li>
        </ul>
        </dd>
        
      </div>
    
  
</dl>

  <h2 id="opportunity-attributes-6" class="govuk-heading-m app-summary-list-heading">How suppliers will be evaluated</h2>
  
  <p class="govuk-body govuk-!-margin-top-3">All suppliers will be asked to provide a written proposal.</p>
  
  

  

  

  

  

  

  
<dl class="govuk-summary-list app-govuk-summary-list app-govuk-summary-list--top-border govuk-!-margin-bottom-8">
  
    
      <div class="govuk-summary-list__row">
        <dt class="govuk-summary-list__key">
          How many suppliers to evaluate
        </dt>
        <dd class="govuk-summary-list__value">
          5
        </dd>
        
      </div>
    
  
    
      <div class="govuk-summary-list__row">
        <dt class="govuk-summary-list__key">
          Proposal criteria
        </dt>
        <dd class="govuk-summary-list__value">
          <ul class="govuk-list govuk-list--bullet">
          <li>technical solution</li>
          <li>approach and methodology</li>
          <li>how the approach or solution meets user needs</li>
          <li>how the approach and solution meets NHSX’s objectives</li>
          <li>estimated time-frames for the work</li>
          <li>how the supplier has identified risks and dependencies and offered approaches to manage them</li>
          <li>team structure</li>
          <li>value for money</li>
        </ul>
        </dd>
        
      </div>
    
  
    
      <div class="govuk-summary-list__row">
        <dt class="govuk-summary-list__key">
          Cultural fit criteria
        </dt>
        <dd class="govuk-summary-list__value">
          <ul class="govuk-list govuk-list--bullet">
          <li>Explain how will you deliver social value? E.g. create new jobs, reduce the disability employment gap, tackle workforce inequality or improve health and well-being. (10%)</li>
          <li>Explain how you will establish trusted advisory relationships with senior stakeholders, include relevant examples where you have done this  in large, complex organisations (4%)</li>
          <li>Propose a style and approach to working with a multidisciplinary in-house team and how you will build in house skills and capabilities (3%)</li>
          <li>Propose your style and approach to working transparently &amp; collaboratively when making decisions and recommendations (3%)</li>
        </ul>
        </dd>
        
      </div>
    
  
    
      <div class="govuk-summary-list__row">
        <dt class="govuk-summary-list__key">
          Payment approach
        </dt>
        <dd class="govuk-summary-list__value">
          Capped time and materials
        </dd>
        
      </div>
    
  
    
      <div class="govuk-summary-list__row">
        <dt class="govuk-summary-list__key">
          Additional assessment methods
        </dt>
        <dd class="govuk-summary-list__value">
          Case study
        </dd>
        
      </div>
    
  
    
      <div class="govuk-summary-list__row">
        <dt class="govuk-summary-list__key">
          Evaluation weighting
        </dt>
        <dd class="govuk-summary-list__value">
          <p class="govuk-body govuk-!-margin-top-0 govuk-!-margin-bottom-1">Technical competence</p>
        <div>50%</div>
        <p class="govuk-body govuk-!-margin-top-3 govuk-!-margin-bottom-1">Cultural fit</p>
        <div>20%</div>
        <p class="govuk-body govuk-!-margin-top-3 govuk-!-margin-bottom-1">Price</p>
        <div>30%</div>
        </dd>
        
      </div>
    
  
</dl>

  </div>
</div>
<div class="govuk-grid-row">
  <div class="govuk-grid-column-full">
    

<h2 id="clarification-questions" class="govuk-heading-m app-summary-list-heading">Questions asked by suppliers</h2>



  

  

  

  

  

  

  

  

  

  

  

  

  

  

  

  

  

  

  

  
<dl class="govuk-summary-list app-govuk-summary-list app-govuk-summary-list--top-border govuk-!-margin-bottom-8">
  
    
      <div class="govuk-summary-list__row">
        <dt class="govuk-summary-list__key">
          1. &#34;A phase of work for the Digital Child Health programme took place during 2019/20 and partially into 2020/21. This work did not deliver the required outcomes and was subsequently closed before the current programme was opened.”<br>Were there any third-party suppliers involved in the initial programme?
        </dt>
        <dd class="govuk-summary-list__value">
          NHS Digital led this work. No discovery was completed, although some user research took place. Some ad-hoc work for minor support was also commissioned from other private and third sector suppliers.
        </dd>
        
      </div>
    
  
    
      <div class="govuk-summary-list__row">
        <dt class="govuk-summary-list__key">
          2. Which third-party suppliers were involved in the initial discovery?
        </dt>
        <dd class="govuk-summary-list__value">
          NHS Digital led this work. No discovery was completed, although some user research took place. Some ad-hoc work for minor support was also commissioned from other private and third sector suppliers.
        </dd>
        
      </div>
    
  
    
      <div class="govuk-summary-list__row">
        <dt class="govuk-summary-list__key">
          3. Please can you state who did the initial work for this opportunity during 2019/20 and partially into 2020/21?
        </dt>
        <dd class="govuk-summary-list__value">
          NHS Digital led this work. No discovery was completed, although some user research took place. Some ad-hoc work for minor support was also commissioned from other private and third sector suppliers.
        </dd>
        
      </div>
    
  
    
      <div class="govuk-summary-list__row">
        <dt class="govuk-summary-list__key">
          4. Is there an existing platform that this digital solution will be built upon or does a new platform require construction?
        </dt>
        <dd class="govuk-summary-list__value">
          NHS Digital platforms are under review. The final set of solutions are not entirely within the gift of the NHS. This programme involves working with third party maternity and child health system suppliers, along with the developers of apps and other front end interfaces for pregnant women, children and families.
        </dd>
        
      </div>
    
  
    
      <div class="govuk-summary-list__row">
        <dt class="govuk-summary-list__key">
          5. Based upon previous work, can you share the likely integration complexity anticipated to get to and through Alpha?
        </dt>
        <dd class="govuk-summary-list__value">
          Work done to date was not detailed or complete enough to make that assessment.
        </dd>
        
      </div>
    
  
    
      <div class="govuk-summary-list__row">
        <dt class="govuk-summary-list__key">
          6. Will the team be required to conduct all business change activities as part of this transformation?
        </dt>
        <dd class="govuk-summary-list__value">
          Not all business change activities. Some will be handled by NHSX.
        </dd>
        
      </div>
    
  
    
      <div class="govuk-summary-list__row">
        <dt class="govuk-summary-list__key">
          7. For Alpha, is it envisaged that there will be a restricted initial user base, one trust, for example?
        </dt>
        <dd class="govuk-summary-list__value">
          the initial work package will be for discovery, which will help inform the user base. It is unlikely the user base will be restricted to one Trust.
        </dd>
        
      </div>
    
  
    
      <div class="govuk-summary-list__row">
        <dt class="govuk-summary-list__key">
          8. In regards to Q3 can you please define what you class as “high volume”
        </dt>
        <dd class="govuk-summary-list__value">
          Something of equivalent volume to the requirement, i.e. the population in England who are stakeholders in Child Health and Maternity.
        </dd>
        
      </div>
    
  
    
      <div class="govuk-summary-list__row">
        <dt class="govuk-summary-list__key">
          9. A recent market engagement was undertaken including an RFI, how is this informing the technology selection and have any decisions already been taken on products?
        </dt>
        <dd class="govuk-summary-list__value">
          The RFI was to understand the maternity system and front end interface landscape. This programme involves working with third party maternity and child health system suppliers, along with the developers of apps and other front end interfaces for pregnant women, children and families. NHSX are not selecting products, that is within the gift of the NHS Provider Trusts.
        </dd>
        
      </div>
    
  
    
      <div class="govuk-summary-list__row">
        <dt class="govuk-summary-list__key">
          10. Can you provide more detail on the leadership and structure of the existing team – which disciplines are represented e.g. Product, User Research, Delivery Management etc?
        </dt>
        <dd class="govuk-summary-list__value">
          NHSX will be leading a blended team of NHSX, NHSD, NHSE/I, PHE and others including third party suppliers. NHSX will provide the programme leadership including: senior programme management, lead architect, lead service designer, lead user researcher and senior implementation lead. The delivery partner we are looking to procure for discovery and alpha will provide the architecture, service design, user research and business analysis capabilities. A separate delivery partner is being procured for PMO and delivery management.
        </dd>
        
      </div>
    
  
    
      <div class="govuk-summary-list__row">
        <dt class="govuk-summary-list__key">
          11. What information is available for us to base our recommendation on the technical solution – is there an existing technical stack in place? And will there be enough information available to provide this ahead of Discovery or shouldn’t this be an output of Discovery?
        </dt>
        <dd class="govuk-summary-list__value">
          Output of discovery. Part of the specified discovery work package will be to assess any collateral that exists.
        </dd>
        
      </div>
    
  
    
      <div class="govuk-summary-list__row">
        <dt class="govuk-summary-list__key">
          12. What were the limitations and shortcomings of the Digital Child Health programme that led to its discontinuation?
        </dt>
        <dd class="govuk-summary-list__value">
          The scope of the Child Health aspect has changed since the previous work was undertaken.
        </dd>
        
      </div>
    
  
    
      <div class="govuk-summary-list__row">
        <dt class="govuk-summary-list__key">
          13. Where will patient data be stored? Will it be centrally held or in individual trusts/ICS? Where will the system be hosted?
        </dt>
        <dd class="govuk-summary-list__value">
          NHS Digital will be building the infrastructure to facilitate the ability for patient data to be viewed by approved persons anywhere in England. The successful supplier will provide expertise in making a joint technical decision with NHS Digital partners. the final decision will be informed by the discovery work package.
        </dd>
        
      </div>
    
  
    
      <div class="govuk-summary-list__row">
        <dt class="govuk-summary-list__key">
          14. Will access to existing patient record systems be made available for interoperability?
        </dt>
        <dd class="govuk-summary-list__value">
          One of the programme goals is to enable fully interoperable digital personal health records, the successful supplier will be required to complete discovery and alpha to this end.
        </dd>
        
      </div>
    
  
    
      <div class="govuk-summary-list__row">
        <dt class="govuk-summary-list__key">
          15. What is meant by “potentially” service providers – is this seen primarily as interaction between data and patient?
        </dt>
        <dd class="govuk-summary-list__value">
          Service Provider = NHS Provider Trusts in this context. At go-live the product(s) may enable patients and clinicians to interact with the data. Subject to the outcome of the discovery and alpha.
        </dd>
        
      </div>
    
  
    
      <div class="govuk-summary-list__row">
        <dt class="govuk-summary-list__key">
          16. What was the cause of the failed outcomes, was it technical or process issues? Are there any learnings that can help avoid the same mistakes?
        </dt>
        <dd class="govuk-summary-list__value">
          Change of scope.
        </dd>
        
      </div>
    
  
    
      <div class="govuk-summary-list__row">
        <dt class="govuk-summary-list__key">
          17. Are there existing services/platforms that the solution will need to integrate with eg Foundation Suppliers, NHS App etc
        </dt>
        <dd class="govuk-summary-list__value">
          Subject to outcome of discovery.
        </dd>
        
      </div>
    
  
    
      <div class="govuk-summary-list__row">
        <dt class="govuk-summary-list__key">
          18. Are you able to provide a resource profile of the team roles you require, i.e. not covered by existing team members?
        </dt>
        <dd class="govuk-summary-list__value">
          NHSX will be leading a blended team of NHSX, NHSD, NHSE/I, PHE and others including third party suppliers. NHSX will provide the programme leadership including: senior programme management, lead architect, lead service designer, lead user researcher and senior implementation lead. The delivery partner we are looking to procure for discovery and alpha will provide the architecture, service design, user research and business analysis capabilities. A separate delivery partner is being procured for PMO and delivery management.
        </dd>
        
      </div>
    
  
    
      <div class="govuk-summary-list__row">
        <dt class="govuk-summary-list__key">
          19. How many teams do you envisage may potentially run concurrently?
        </dt>
        <dd class="govuk-summary-list__value">
          This has as yet not been envisaged. Currently theprogramme has 4 main workstreams: 1) future operating model, 2) citizen empowerment. 3) digital maturity 4) patient safety and data. However the successful supplier should take into account that there is a maternity part and child health part to the programme, some of which heavily overlap.
        </dd>
        
      </div>
    
  
    
      <div class="govuk-summary-list__row">
        <dt class="govuk-summary-list__key">
          20. Who would be responsible for recruitment of users for research?
        </dt>
        <dd class="govuk-summary-list__value">
          NHSX, PHE and NHS England &amp; Improvement.
        </dd>
        
      </div>
    
  
</dl>



  </div>
</div>





